Title: Veggie Roast And Tuna Salad
Ingredients: {'Salad Dressing:': ['2 teaspoons tahini', '1 ½ teaspoons harissa paste', '1 ½ teaspoons pomegranate molasses', '1 tablespoon brine, from pickled olives', 'salt, as needed'], 'Salad Ingredients:': ['1 cup tuna (200 g), canned', '1 red bell pepper, cubed', '2 ½ cups brussels sprouts (250 g), cut into halves', '1 tablespoon olive oil', '1 tablespoon Za’atar spice mix', '2 teaspoons balsamic vinegar', 'salt, to taste'], 'For Garnish:': ['1 handful fresh parsley', '2 teaspoons Za’atar', '2 teaspoons balsamic vinegar', '1 teaspoon red chili flakes', '2 cloves garlic, cut into thin slivers', '1 shallot, sliced thin', '2 teaspoons caper', '1 tablespoon olive oil', '¾ cup bread croutons, toasted, dressed with extra virgin olive oil and a pinch of salt']}
Preparation: {1: 'Roast the brussel sprouts and bell pepper with za’atar, salt, olive oil and balsamic vinegar at 400°F for 25-30 minutes or more, depending on how charred you like your veggies.', 2: 'Once the veggies are roasted, take a salad bowl and mix the sprouts, bell pepper and canned tuna together. Then, mix together dressing ingredients and, once combined, toss salad in this.', 3: 'Fry a few capers and slivers of small onions and garlic in olive oil and add this on top of the salad.', 4: 'Finish the salad with a final dash of balsamic vinegar, toasted bread croutons, a sprinkle of fresh parsley, za’atar spice mix and red chilli flakes.'}

Title: Giant Chocolate Chip Cookies
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 sticks unsalted butter, cold, chopped into small cubes', '½ cup granulated sugar (100 g)', '1 cup light brown sugar (200 g)', '2 large eggs', '1 teaspoon vanilla extract', '1 ½ cups all purpose flour (185 g)', '1 ½ cups cake flour (185 g)', '1 teaspoon cornstarch', '¾ teaspoon salt', '¾ teaspoon baking soda', '2 cups semi sweet chocolate chips (350 g)']}
Preparation: {1: 'Preheat the oven to 410°F and line two baking sheets with parchment paper.', 2: 'In a large mixing bowl fitted with a paddle attachment, mix the butter with the granulated and brown sugar until light and fluffy.', 3: 'Add eggs one at a time, until fully combined.', 4: 'Add the vanilla extract and mix until fully combined.', 5: 'In a separate bowl, lightly whisk together both flours, baking soda, cornstarch, and salt.', 6: 'Add the dry mixture to the wet mixture until fully combined, and then mix in chocolate chips.', 7: 'Make large balls with the dough, only putting 4 cookies on each pan and leaving space to spread between each cookie.', 8: 'Bake for 9-12 minutes, or until lightly-browned on the top.', 9: 'Let cool for 10 minutes and then enjoy!'}

Title: Chipotle Chili And Cornbread Dumplings
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 lb ground beef (905 g)', '2 tablespoons kosher salt', '1 tablespoon black pepper', '1 tablespoon ground cumin', '1 tablespoon chilli powder', '1 tablespoon smoked paprika, ground', '1 teaspoon cayenne', '1 large onion, chopped', '1 red bell pepper, chopped', '6 cloves garlic, minced', '2 chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, chopped', '12 oz tomato paste (340 g)', '2 cups beef broth (480 mL)', '12 oz chopped tomato (340 g), 1 can', '15 oz black beans (425 g), 1 can', '15 oz red kidney bean (425 g), 1 can', '1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar, optional'], 'Cornbread Dumplings': ['1 cup cornmeal (120 g)', '1 cup flour (125 g)', '1 teaspoon baking powder', '1 pinch salt', '2 eggs', '¼ cup honey (85 g)', '½ cup buttermilk (120 mL)']}
Preparation: {1: 'In a large bowl, mix the flour, cornmeal, baking powder, and salt. Mix and make a little well in the center.', 2: 'Add the milk, eggs, honey into the well, beat the eggs and liquid first, and then combine with the rest of the dry ingredients. Set aside until chili is almost finished.', 3: 'In a large pot at medium high heat, add the beef, season with salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, smoked paprika, cayenne, and cook until it is a deep brown color.', 4: 'Add the onion, red bell peppers garlic, and chopped chipotles, and a pinch of salt. Cook until caramelized and soft, about 10 minutes.', 5: 'Add the tomato paste and cook until the tomato paste gets dark and starts sticking to the bottom slightly.', 6: 'Add in the canned diced tomatoes, beef broth, black beans, kidney beans, and apple cider vinegar (optional). Stir until all is well incorporated. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low to a simmer,', 7: 'Scoop and shape the cornbread batter into golf ball sized dumplings and place in the simmering chili.', 8: 'Put a lid on the Chili and steam/simmer the dumplings 20 minutes or until the dumplings are cooked through.', 9: 'Serve with cheddar cheese, sour cream, and sliced scallions.', 10: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Nut-Free Macarons
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 large egg whites', '4 tablespoons granulated sugar, plus 1/2 teaspoon', '½ cup all purpose flour (65 g)', '½ cup powdered sugar (55 g)', '½ teaspoon vanilla extract', 'gel food coloring, optional', 'buttercream frosting, or any frosting of your choice']}
Preparation: {1: 'In a bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.', 2: 'Gradually add the granulated sugar until stiff peaks form.', 3: 'In a separate bowl, whisk the flour and powdered sugar together. Then, sift the flour and powdered sugar mixture into the egg white mixture.', 4: 'Add the vanilla extract, and gel food coloring if you want the macarons to be colored.', 5: 'Gently fold all the ingredients together.', 6: 'Transfer the batter into a piping bag with a rounded tip.', 7: 'Pipe the macarons onto a baking sheet with parchment paper. Gently tap the baking sheet on a flat surface a few times to release air bubbles.', 8: 'Let the macarons sit at room temperature for about 45 minutes.', 9: 'Preheat the oven to 280°F.', 10: 'Bake the macarons for 17-20 minutes.', 11: 'Allow the macarons to cool for 10 minutes, then transfer the macarons on to a cooling rack.', 12: 'Add a dollop of buttercream or any frosting of your choice to one of the macaron shells, then top it with another macaron shell to create a sandwich. Repeat with the remaining shells and frosting.', 13: 'For best results, allow the macarons to “bloom” for about 24 hours.', 14: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Grain-Free Chocolate Chip Cookie Bars
Ingredients: {'General': ['nonstick cooking spray, for greasing', '1 stick butter, melted, plus 2 tablespoons', '1 cup honey (336 g)', '2 teaspoons vanilla', '5 large eggs, beaten', '3 ½ cups blanched almond flour (336 g)', '¾ teaspoon salt', '¼ teaspoon baking powder', '1 bag dark chocolate chip']}
Preparation: {1: 'Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C), and generously spray a 9 x 13 inch (22 x 33 cm) rectangular cake pan.', 2: 'Combine everything but the chocolate chips until well-incorporated (I usually just whisk, wet ingredients first, and then dry).', 3: 'Stir in the chocolate chips.', 4: 'Spread batter evenly into pan.', 5: 'Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out barely clean. These might brown a lot on edges, but that’s okay.', 6: 'Cool completely before cutting!', 7: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Caribbean Rice
Ingredients: {'General': ['½ lb pork shoulder (300 g), diced', '7 oz chorizo (200 g), sliced', '1 sour orange, juiced', '4 cloves garlic, chopped', '¼ cup fresh cilantro (10 g)', '½ cup red onion (75 g), chopped', '½ cup red pepper (50 g), chopped', '2 cups rice (400 g), pre-cooked', '1 ½ cups black beans (210 g), boiled', '½ teaspoon black pepper', '½ teaspoon salt', '2 cups water (240 mL), used to boiled beans', '1 can coconut milk']}
Preparation: {1: 'In a large pan, cook the pork, chorizo, and orange juice. Remove from the pan, leaving the grease behind.', 2: 'Take the remaining grease and mix it with garlic, cilantro, onion, and pepper and have it cook for 5 minutes at medium heat.', 3: 'Add the pork and chorizo to the mixture, then add the rice and beans.', 4: 'Add the salt and pepper to the mix and the water from the beans. Let it cook for 15 minutes until the rice is cooked, adding water if needed.', 5: 'Add the can of coconut milk and stir everything for 5 more minutes.', 6: 'Serve and eat up!!!'}

Title: Sweet And Sour Eggplant
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 medium eggplant', '½ cup oil (120 mL), divided', '1 tablespoon cumin seed', '2 tablespoons garlic, chopped', '1 ½ cups onion (225 g), chopped', '2 tablespoons red pepper flakes', '1 cup ketchup (240 g)', '1 cup vinegar (237 mL)', '1 tablespoon salt', 'water, as needed', '⅓ cup fresh coriander (15 g)', 'rice, for serving']}
Preparation: {1: 'Cut the eggplant into medium sized pieces.', 2: 'In a frying pan, put some oil and lightly fry the eggplant pieces. Remove them from the pan.', 3: 'Using the same fry pan, add some oil. Then, add the cumin seeds and chopped garlic. Fry for 15 seconds, then add the onion and red pepper flakes. Fry for 3 minutes. Add the eggplants and stir it. Add the ketchup and mix it well.', 4: 'Add the vinegar and mix it. Cover the pan and keep on low heat for 8 minutes. Take off the lid, then add the salt and a little bit of water (if necessary). Cook for 4 minutes without the lid.', 5: 'Sprinkle the coriander over and turn off the heat.', 6: 'Serve with plain rice or biriyani.'}

Title: Grandma Decanini's Zuppa Pavese
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 qt chicken broth', '2 tablespoons dried parsley', '2 teaspoons butter', '2 thick slices good Italian bread', '2 eggs', '¼ cup grated parmesan cheese, plus more to taste', 'salt, to taste', 'pepper, to taste']}
Preparation: {1: 'In a small pot put 1 quart chicken broth and 2 tbsp dried parsley. Bring to a low boil, then turn down to a simmer.', 2: 'In a frying pan add a knob of butter and grill both sides of bread until nice and crunchy. Slice in half and arrange in oven-safe bowl.', 3: 'Crack 1 or 2 eggs over the bread so as not to break yolks. Add salt and pepper and a dash of parsley.', 4: 'Slowly ladle or pour simmering broth over eggs and bread, do not break yolk!', 5: 'Add Parmesan cheese and bake at 350°F (180°C) for 20-25 minutes for soft-boiled eggs, longer if you want the yolk harder. Add more broth and cheese fresh out of the oven.'}

Title: Apple Pie French Toast
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 eggs', '1 cup milk (240 mL)', '1 teaspoon cinnamon', '½ teaspoon salt', '1 teaspoon vanilla', '2 tablespoons brown sugar', '1 medium grated apple, divided', '2 tablespoons butter', '7 breads', 'almond and cashew, for serving', 'maple syrup, for serving']}
Preparation: {1: 'Whisk together eggs, milk, cinnamon, salt, vanilla, and brown sugar.', 2: 'Add ¾ of the grated apple to the egg mixture and fold it in.', 3: 'Coat bread slices with the egg and apple mixture. Pan fry in butter on medium flame for about 1 minute on each side (or until nicely toasted).', 4: 'Serve with the remaining grated apple, crushed nuts and a drizzle of maple syrup.', 5: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Quick And Easy Leftover Rotisserie Chicken Alfredo
Ingredients: {'General': ['2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken (250 g), shredded', '½ egg noodle, cooked', '1 jar alfredo sauce, 16 oz (455 G)', '⅓ cup milk (80 mL)', '2 tablespoons butter', '¼ teaspoon salt', '½ teaspoon garlic powder', '½ teaspoon oregano', '½ teaspoon poultry seasoning', '½ teaspoon dried parsley']}
Preparation: {1: 'Boil egg noodles and cook according to package directions. Drain. Set aside.', 2: 'In a 2 quart saucepan over medium heat, combine leftover chicken, Alfredo sauce, milk, butter, salt, garlic powder, poultry seasoning, oregano, and parsley flakes. Stir often for about 10 minutes, or until sauce is thick, creamy, and hot.', 3: 'Serve the chicken alfredo over egg noodles.', 4: 'Garnish with chopped parsley flakes.'}

Title: Super Easy Roasted Spicy Cauliflower
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 small cauliflower, cut into florets', '2 tablespoons chili sauce', '1 tablespoon garlic powder', '1 tablespoon lime juice', 'salt, to taste']}
Preparation: {1: 'Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).', 2: 'Toss florets in hot / chili sauce. Add other ingredients. Mix.', 3: 'Bake for 20-25 minutes, or until the cauliflower turns brown and crispy. Keep checking along the way. Be careful not to burn it.', 4: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Kam’s Chocolate Pie
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 premade pie crust, 8 in (20 cm)', '¾ cup sugar (150 g)', '1 pinch salt', '1 tablespoon cornstarch', '1 tablespoon cocoa powder', '2 egg yolks', '1 can evaporated milk, 12 ounce (340 G)', '1 teaspoon vanilla extract', '1 tablespoon butter']}
Preparation: {1: 'Pre-bake the 8 inch (20 cm) pie crust at 400°F (200°C) for 10–12 minutes, or until golden brown. Let cool completely.', 2: 'In a double boiler over medium heat, whisk together the sugar, salt, cornstarch, cocoa powder, and egg yolks until blended and crumbly. Slowly whisk in the can of evaporated milk and vanilla extract until smooth and creamy. Finally put in butter and continue to whisk frequently until filling is thick like pudding.', 3: 'Once thick, pour into your already baked pie crust and let sit for several hours or for best results the next day.', 4: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Baked Chicken Tikka
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 cup plain yogurt (285 g)', '½ tablespoon red chili powder', '½ tablespoon ground coriander', '½ tablespoon ground cumin', '1 teaspoon ground tumeric', '½ teaspoon garam masala', '2 tablespoons lemon juice', '½ teaspoon dried fenugreek leaves', '1 bunch fresh cilantro stem, crushed', '½ tablespoon salt', '1 ½ tablespoons ginger garlic paste', '2 red food colorings', '4 chicken leg quarters, cut into two']}
Preparation: {1: 'Combine all ingredients in a bowl except chicken.', 2: 'Make long slits on chicken with a knife.', 3: 'Put the chicken in the marinade overnight.', 4: 'Bake at 450°F (230°C) for 50 minutes..', 5: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Bruschetta Chicken
Ingredients: {'General': ['4 chicken breasts, (or 2 large, split horizontally) or 2 diced chicken breasts'], 'Chicken Marinade': ['2 teaspoons garlic, (fresh or puréed)', '1 teaspoon salt', '½ teaspoon pepper', '3 teaspoons italian seasoning', '2 teaspoons olive oil'], 'Bruschetta': ['3 medium tomatoes, diced', '¼ red onion, chopped', '1 clove garlic, grated', 'salt, to taste', '2 tablespoons olive oil', '4 tablespoons fresh basil'], 'Balsamic Glaze': ['½ cup balsamic vinegar (120 mL)', '½ cup shredded parmesan cheese (55 g), for topping']}
Preparation: {1: 'Combine chicken and marinade ingredients and set aside.', 2: 'Combine bruschetta ingredients.', 3: 'Place balsamic vinegar in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to simmer for 8-10 minutes, until mixture has thickened and formed a glaze (be careful not to over-reduce).', 4: 'Cook chicken in a large skillet over high heat about 5-6 minutes per side. Once cooked, top with bruschetta, a drizzle of balsamic glaze, and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.', 5: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Sweet Lemon Mousse With Granola Crumble
Ingredients: {'Mousse': ['2 cups sweet lemon juice (480 mL), from medium sweet lemons', '¼ cup sugar (60 g), or to taste', '1 tablespoon lemon juice', '1 teaspoon lemon zest', '½ teaspoon cornstarch, or corn flour', '½ teaspoon water', '2 cups whipping cream (480 mL)', '½ vanilla bean pod'], 'Crumble': ['½ cup mixed dried fruit (75 g)', '½ cup dry oat (50 g)', '4 tablespoons honey', '¼ cup butter (60 g), cubed and chilled', '4 tablespoons wheat flour'], 'For Serving': ['medium sweet lemon cup', 'fresh leaf', 'cubed sweet lemon']}
Preparation: {1: 'Make the mousse: In a sauce pan, add sweet lemon juice and sugar and let the mixture come to a simmer.', 2: 'Add the lemon juice and lemon zest to the pan and let the mixture come to a', 3: 'boil.', 4: 'In a separate bowl, mix the cornstarch and water.', 5: 'Once the sweet lemon mixture comes to a boil, add the cornstarch water to it and', 6: 'mix continuously. Let the mixture thicken until it coats the back of a spoon. Take it off the heat.', 7: 'In a medium-sized bowl, add whipping cream and extract of half a vanilla bean pod. Using a hand mixer or a whisk, whip the cream to stiff peaks.', 8: 'Once the sweet lemon mixture is completely cool to touch, add it to the whipped cream in thirds and fold it gently.', 9: 'Until you are ready to serve, store it in the refrigerator.', 10: 'Make the crumble: In a bowl, add the dried fruits and oats and mix them thoroughly.', 11: 'Add the cubed chilled butter to the mixture and rub it into the mixture with hands. (The heat of the hands slightly melts the butter, making it easier to mix)', 12: 'Add the honey and mix it well.', 13: 'Add the wheat flour and mix it until it coats all the dried fruits and oats mixture.', 14: 'In a baking tray, spread out the mixture and bake it until it turns golden brown. Alternatively, you could also add the mixture to a large pan and mix it continuously to form the crumble on a stove top.', 15: 'Let the mixture completely cool down before serving.', 16: 'To serve, add 1 tsp crumble into the sweet lemon cups and fill in fully with the mousse.', 17: 'Garnish it with fresh leaves and cubes sweet lemon.'}

Title: Vegan Crumble Muffins
Ingredients: {'Muffins': ['½ cup canola oil, or vegetable oil', '½ cup vegan buttermilk, mix 1/2 cup of non-dairy milk, such as almond or soy, and 1/2 tsp of apple cider vinegar and rest for 10 minutes', '½ cup brown sugar', '¼ cup granulated sugar', '2 vegan eggs, I used Bob’s Red Mill Egg Replacer but you can use flax eggs or any egg replacer of your preference', '1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract', '2 cups all-purpose flour, or gluten-free flour', '2 teaspoons baking powder', '1 teaspoon cinnamon', '½ teaspoon salt', '1 ½ cups chopped apple, or pear, or 1 cup cranberries or blueberries, or fruit of choice'], 'Crumble': ['3 tablespoons vegan butter, or coconut oil, melted', '6 tablespoons brown sugar', '1 tablespoon granulated sugar', '½ cup all-purpose flour', '2 tablespoons rolled oats', '1 dash cinnamon']}
Preparation: {1: 'Preheat your oven to 375° F (190°C) and line a muffin tin with paper liners or grease and flour.', 2: 'In a bowl whisk oil, buttermilk, and both of the sugar until they are dissolved.', 3: 'Mix in the eggs and the vanilla extract until they are well incorporated.', 4: 'Separately, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.', 5: 'Mix the dry ingredients to the wet ones gradually until just combined, don’t over mix.', 6: 'Fold in the apples or the fruit of your choice.', 7: 'Divide the batter in the muffin tin, use a ice cream scoop or a ¼ cup measurement.', 8: 'For the crumble, mix the melted butter with the sugars, then add the flour, oats, and cinnamon. Mix it with a spoon or a fork if you want until crumble pieces form.', 9: 'Top the muffins with the crumble mixture evenly.', 10: 'Bake the muffins for 25 minutes or until a toothpick comes clean after inserted in the center of your muffins.', 11: 'Allow muffins to cool before eating.'}

Title: Paneer Butter Masala
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 teaspoon vegetable oil', '1 green chilli, chopped', '1 ginger, chopped', '6 cloves garlic, chopped', '2 onions, roughly chopped', '1 cup tomato (250 g), chopped', '¼ cup water (60 mL), plus 6 tablespoons, divided', '¼ cup cashews (30 g), soaked in water', '1 teaspoon kashmiri, chili powder', '1 butter, small knob', '1 teaspoon coriander powder', '2 tablespoons heavy cream', '½ teaspoon garam masala powder', '2 ½ cups paneer (250 g)', '1 teaspoon dried fenugreek leaves', 'salt, to taste', 'coriander leaf, chopped, to taste', 'flatbread, or rice, for serving']}
Preparation: {1: 'Heat a pan and add the vegetable oil. Add the cinnamon stick, green chili, ginger, garlic, and onions then cook it until onions are little translucent on medium flame.', 2: 'Then add in your tomatoes and cook it for 3-5 minutes, or until tomatoes are tender, then turn the flame off and put a lid on it for 5 minutes.', 3: 'Put the tomatoes and onion mixture in a blender and blitz the mixture with 1 tablespoon water into a smooth paste.', 4: 'Strain the tomato purée and set it aside, then add in your soaked cashews in same blender with 5 tablespoons of water and blend it into a creamy cashew paste.', 5: 'Heat the same pan with a knob of butter, melt It, and add in your Kashmiri chili powder (stir it) and cook it for 10 seconds. Add in your tomato onion purée in it and mix properly and bring it to a boil.', 6: 'Add your coriander powder in it, mix it, and cover the pot and cook it for 3 minutes on medium flame.', 7: 'Then add in your cashews paste with ¼ cup of water mix it properly and cook it for 3 minutes.', 8: 'Stir in your cream and garam masala. Then add in your paneer cubes mix it and cook the curry for 5 minutes on low flame.', 9: 'Add in your fenugreek leaves and mix it. Season with salt to taste.', 10: 'Lastly garnish the dish with little cream on top with coriander leaves and serve it with flatbreads or rice.', 11: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Anacortes Carrot Ginger Soup
Ingredients: {'General': ['6 medium carrots', '2 small sweet potatoes', '1 ginger root', '1 yellow onion', '1 pasilla chile', '3 cloves garlic, minced', 'olive oil, to taste', '1 box vegetable stock', '1 teaspoon paprika', 'red pepper flake, to taste', 'salt, to taste', 'pepper, to taste', 'pepita, optional, for topping']}
Preparation: {1: 'Peel and dice the carrots, sweet potatoes and ginger. Dice onion and seed and dice the pasilla pepper. Mince garlic.', 2: 'Heat olive oil in soup pot over medium heat. Add onions, garlic, ginger and pasilla pepper. Sauté until translucent and fragrant, 3-5 minutes.', 3: 'Add carrots and sweet potatoes and cover in vegetable stock. Add paprika and red pepper flakes to desired heat. Bring to a boil, cover, and lower heat to a simmer. Cook covered for 35-40 minutes.', 4: 'Using an immersion blender, blend soup until smooth. Season with salt and pepper to taste.', 5: 'Garnish with pepitas and serve.', 6: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Vegan Snickerdoodle Cupcakes
Ingredients: {'Dry Ingredients': ['1 ½ cups all purpose flour (185 g)', '¾ cup brown sugar (150 g)', '¼ cup white sugar (50 g)', '1 teaspoon cinnamon', '½ teaspoon baking soda', '½ teaspoon salt'], 'Wet Ingredients': ['¾ cup cold water (180 mL)', '½ cup vegetable oil (120 mL)', '2 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract', '1 teaspoon apple cider vinegar'], 'Frosting': ['2 cups powdered sugar (220 g)', '½ cup vegan butter (115 g)', '½ cup vegetable shortening (120 mL)', '½ teaspoon vanilla extract', '1 tablespoon nondairy milk', '1 tablespoon white sugar', '1 tablespoon cinnamon']}
Preparation: {1: 'Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a cupcake pan with 12 liners.', 2: 'In a large bowl combine all the dry ingredients. Whisk together until well combined.', 3: 'In a medium bowl combine the wet ingredients. Mix well.', 4: 'Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients. Using a spatula mix everything together until just combined. No need to worry about lumps so don’t over mix!', 5: 'Divide batter evenly between the liners. Bake for 18-20 minutes until the center cupcakes are golden and a toothpick comes out clean.', 6: 'Remove cupcakes from pan and refrigerate until completely cool.', 7: 'While cooling, make the frosting! Combine the powdered sugar, vegan butter, vegetable shortening and vanilla extract using a stand or hand mixer. Add in non-dairy milk one tablespoon at a time until you achieve the desired consistency.', 8: 'In a small bowl mix together sugar and cinnamon.', 9: 'Once the cupcakes are cool, frost, and sprinkle the cinnamon sugar on the cupcakes.', 10: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Co-Keto (Puerto Rican Coconut Eggnog)
Ingredients: {'General': ['4 egg yolks, beaten', '2 cups heavy whipping cream (480 mL)', '1 oz coconut oil (25 g)', '2 cans cream of coconut, 27 ounces (765 grams)', '1 can unsweetened coconut milk, 13.5 ounces (380 grams)', '1 cup rum (240 mL)', '½ cup warm water (120 mL)', '¼ teaspoon ground cloves', '2 teaspoons ground cinnamon', '¼ teaspoon ground nutmeg', '¼ teaspoon ground ginger', '1 tablespoon vanilla extract', 'keto-friendly sweetener of choice, such as stevia, splenda, or monkfruit, to taste']}
Preparation: {1: 'In a double boiler, combine the egg yolks and heavy whipping cream . Stirring constantly, warm over lightly simmering water until the mixture reaches a 160°F (71°C). Slowly drip in the coconut oil to emulsify. The mix should be smooth and creamy. It should be able to coat the back of a spoon.', 2: 'Add the mix to a blender with the cream of coconut, unsweetened coconut milk, rum, water, spices (or use 2 tablespoons pumpkin pie spice), and vanilla. Blend until smooth. Taste and sweeten to your liking using your preferred keto-friendly sweetener. Pour into glass bottles and chill.', 3: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Fenugreek Grape Pickle
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 cup fenugreek (100 g)', '4 tablespoons sesame oil', '1 ½ teaspoons black mustard seeds', '1 teaspoon asafoetida', '1 teaspoon salt, or to taste, divided', '1 cup sweet fresh seedless grapes (100 g)', '1 tablespoon red chile powder, heaping', '½ cup medium concentrate tamarind juice (120 mL), diluted tamarind paste or powder, 2 tablespoons lemon or lime juice, or 1 tablespoon vinegar', '2 tablespoons jaggery, brown sugar, or honey']}
Preparation: {1: 'Soak the fenugreek seeds in water for 24 hours. Drain, wrap loosely in a cotton cloth, and keep covered in a bowl for another 24 hours. The seeds should have sprouted.', 2: 'Heat the sesame oil in a non-stick pan. When hot, add the mustard seeds.', 3: 'After the mustard seeds splutter, add the asafoetida and sprouted fenugreek.', 4: 'Add half the salt amount, mix, cover, and cook for 5-7 minutes on medium heat.', 5: 'Now add the grapes, the remaining salt, and the chile powder. Cover and cook for another 5 minutes.', 6: 'Add the tamarind juice, mix, and keep covered for another 3 minutes.', 7: 'Take off the lid, add the jaggery, and simmer until the oil starts to float on the top (should be about 5 mins).', 8: 'Serve or store for up to 6 months!', 9: 'Note: To enhance the flavor, you can use dry red chiles instead of store-bought chile powder. Use 8 chiles for this quantity of pickle and add it to the oil at the beginning (before you add the mustard seeds). Fry for just about 45 seconds on low heat. Take just the chiles out, leave the oil in the pan and turn off the stove. After the chiles cool down in a few mins, grind them into a powder. Make the pickle in the chile-infused oil you already have in your pan with the chile powder you have just made.', 10: 'Enjoy!'}

Title: Beef Shawarma Fries

Title: Choco Chip Cookies
Ingredients: {'General': ['1 cup brown sugar', '1 cup caster sugar', '1 stick Amul butter', '2 eggs', '2 teaspoons vanilla extract', '1 teaspoon baking powder', '¼ teaspoon salt', '3 cups maida flour', '1 cup dark chocolate chip', 'butter, to grease the pan']}
